Hardcoded vanity numbers (350+, 12) in `SocialProof` violated the "no invented stats" rule. Replaced with live Supabase head-count queries; stats only render when count > 0.

## New hook — `src/hooks/use-public-stats.ts`
- Single `usePublicStats()` fires 4 parallel `head: true / count: "exact"` queries via `Promise.all`
- Tables: `destinations` (`is_published=true`), `blog_posts` (`is_published=true`), `quiz_responses`, `newsletter_subscribers`
- `staleTime: 30 min`; any Supabase error propagates → `data` stays `undefined` → component renders nothing rather than a broken number

```ts
export function usePublicStats() {
  return useQuery<PublicStats>({
    queryKey: ["public-stats"],
    staleTime: 30 * 60 * 1000,
    queryFn: async () => {
      const [destinations, blogPosts, quizResponses, newsletterSubscribers] =
        await Promise.all([
          fetchCount("destinations", { column: "is_published", value: true }),
          fetchCount("blog_posts",   { column: "is_published", value: true }),
          fetchCount("quiz_responses"),
          fetchCount("newsletter_subscribers"),
        ]);
      return { destinations, blogPosts, quizResponses, newsletterSubscribers };
    },
  });
}
```

## Updated — `src/components/landing/SocialProof.tsx`
- Consumes `usePublicStats()`; each data-driven stat card is conditionally rendered only if its count > 0
- Returns `null` while loading — prevents a flash of zeros before real counts arrive
- TAP certification card is unconditional (real credential, no number involved)
- Adds `blogPosts` as a third data stat (was missing before)
